 "id": "CVE-2025-4565",
 "published": "2025-06-16T14:50:40.906Z",
 "modified": "2025-08-14T17:05:37.770Z",
 "summary": "Unbounded recursion in Python Protobuf",
 "details": "Any project that uses Protobuf Pure-Python backend to parse untrusted Protocol Buffers data containing an arbitrary number of recursive groups, recursive messages or a series of SGROUP tags can be corrupted by exceeding the Python recursion limit. This can result in a Denial of service by crashing the application with a RecursionError. We recommend upgrading to version =>6.31.1 or beyond commit 17838beda2943d08b8a9d4df5b68f5f04f26d901",
